<p>I'm trying to build an atom-like (electrons revolving around a nucleus) animation in css and have the electron stop on hover of the cursor. This works fine in Chrome and Firefox, but in Safari the hover action doesn't work at all or only on certain points in the electron's arc.</p>  <p>I've built a fiddle to try it out here: <a href="http://jsfiddle.net/a8vcgpge/" rel="nofollow">http://jsfiddle.net/a8vcgpge/</a></p>  <p>Here's the code as well:</p>  <p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false"> <div class="snippet-code"> <pre class="snippet-code-css lang-css prettyprint-override"><code>#atom {    position: relative;    z-index: 1;   width: 100%; height: 400px;    margin: 5px auto; }  #nucleus {    position: absolute;    top: 50%; left: 50%; z-index: 2;    width: 100px; height: 100px;    margin: -50px 0 0 -50px;    border-radius: 100px;   background: #000;  }  .orbit {    position: absolute;    top: 50%; left: 50%; z-index: 2;    margin: -100px 0 0 -100px;    width: 200px; height: 200px;    border-radius: 200px;   border: 1px solid #000; }  .electron {   position: absolute;   width: 20px; height: 20px;   top: 50%; left: 50%; z-index: 3;   margin: -10px 0 0 -10px;    background: #000;   border-radius: 20px;    -webkit-animation: rot 20s infinite linear;   -webkit-animation-play-state: running;   animation: rot 20s infinite linear;   animation-play-state: running; }  .electron:hover {   -webkit-animation-play-state: paused;   animation-play-state: paused; }  @keyframes rot {   from {     transform: rotate(0deg)                translate(-100px)                rotate(0deg);   }   to {     transform: rotate(360deg)                translate(-100px)                 rotate(-360deg);   } }  @-webkit-keyframes rot {   from {     -webkit-transform: rotate(0deg)                translate(-100px)                rotate(0deg);   }   to {     -webkit-transform: rotate(360deg)                translate(-100px)                 rotate(-360deg);   } }</code></pre> <pre class="snippet-code-html lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;div id="atom"&gt;     &lt;div class="orbit"&gt;         &lt;div class="electron"&gt; E &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;div id="nucleus"&gt; N &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</code></pre> </div> </div> </p>